        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This would violate the documented `dev-pattern`:\r\n\r\n> - When accepting a buffer id, etc., 0 means \"current buffer\", nil means \"all\r\n> buffers\".  Likewise for window id, tabpage id, etc.\r\n> - Examples: |vim.lsp.codelens.clear()| |vim.diagnostic.enable()|\r\n\r\nI thought the conclusion of a previous discussion around this was that we'd first need to go through the `nil = current` cases, and see if they need to be adapted to apply to all buffers. But that needs to be evaluated on a case by case basis, it might not make sense for all of them.\r\n\r\nAt best I think this could be a `return bufnr == 0 and api.nvim_get_current_buf() or bufnr` as a private `vim._get_buf()`, but imho it's not worth the function call and indirection.",
